When the State of Arkansas was chartered , she controlled 'to the center of the river' a most unstable line . 
The State of Mississippi claimed 'to the channel' another shifty and unstable line . 
By and by a cut off threw this big island out of Arkansas , and yet not within Mississippi . 
'Middle of the river' on one side of it , 'channel' on the other . 
That is as I understand the problem . 
One man owns the whole island , and of right is 'the man without a country . 
The river moved it over and joined it to Mississippi . 
A chap established a whiskey shop there , without a Mississippi license , and enriched himself upon Mississippi custom under Arkansas protection . 
