PAGE , Herewith please find the letter kindly loaned me . 
I am afraid its genuineness cannot be established . 
It purports to be addressed to some prisoner here . 
No such letter ever came to a prisoner here . 
All letters received are carefully read by officers of the prison before they go into the hands of the convicts , and any such letter could not be forgotten . 
Again , Charles Williams is not a Christian man , but a dissolute , cunning prodigal , whose father is a minister of the gospel . 
His name is an assumed one . 
